SOURCELONG:Player's Handbook	SOURCESHORT:PHB	SOURCEWEB:http://www.gozzilioni.net	SOURCEDATE:2024-08																													

###Block: Origin Feats
# Feat Name	CATEGORY:	TYPE:	visible	key	Req. Att.	Required Class	Required Feat				Req. nb of Hand	Required Lvl	Required Skill	Req. Spellbook		Required Stat						Var. Min. Value	Special Ability	Define	DESC:	Stackable?	Multiple?	Choose	Automaticaly Gained Armor Prof.	Automaticaly Gained Shield Prof.	Automaticaly Gained Weapon Prof.	Add Spell Lvl	Save checks bonus	Combat bonus	BONUS:DC	Bonus to HP	% bonus to range	Bonus to skill	Modify VAR	Weapon prop. bonus	Weapon prof. bonus	Source Page					
Alert	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Origin	VISIBLE:YES																						DESC:You gain the following benefits. &nl; Initiative Proficiency. When you roll Initiative, you can add your Proficiency Bonus to the roll. &nl; Initiative Swap. Immediately after you roll Initiative, you can swap your Initiative with the Initiative of one willing ally in the same combat. You can't make this swap if you or the ally has the Incapacitated condition.															BONUS:COMBAT|INITIATIVE|ProficiencyBonus|TYPE=Proficiency			SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Crafter	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Origin	VISIBLE:YES																						DESC:You gain the following benefits. &nl; Tool Proficiency. You gain proficiency with three different Artisan's Tools of your choice from the Fast Crafting table. &nl; Discount. Whenever you buy a nonmagical item, you receive a 20 per cent discount on it. &nl; Fast Crafting. When you finish a Long Rest, you can craft one piece of gear from the Fast Crafting table, provided you have the Artisa n's Tools associated w ith that item a n d h ave proficiency w ith those tool s. The item lasts until you fini sh another Long Rest , at which point t he item falls apart.																	BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Artisan's Tools Proficiency|3			SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Healer	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Origin	VISIBLE:YES																						DESC:You gain the following benefits. &nl; Battle Medic. If you have a Healer's Kit, you can expend one use of it and tend to a creature within 5 feet of yourself as a Utilize action. That creature can expend one of its Hit Point Dice, and you then roll that die. The creature regains a number of Hit Points equal to the roll plus your Proficiency Bonus. &nl; Healing Rerolls. Whenever you roll a die to determine the number of Hit Points you restore with a spell or with this feat's Battle Medic benefit, you can reroll the die if it rolls a 1, and you must use the new roll.																				SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Lucky	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Origin	VISIBLE:YES																						DESC:You gain the following benefits. &nl; Luck Points. You have a number of Luck Points equal to your Proficiency Bonus and can spend the points on the benefits below. You regain your expended Luck Points when you finish a Long Rest. &nl; Advantage. When you roll a d20 for a D20 Test, you can spend 1 Luck Point to give yourself Advantage on the roll. &nl; Disadvantage. When a creature rolls a d20 for an attack roll agai nst you, you can spend 1 Luck Point to impose Disadvantage on that roll.	DEFINE:LuckPoints|0																BONUS:VAR|LuckPoints|3			SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Magic Initiate	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Origin	VISIBLE:YES																						DESC:You gain the foll owing benefits. &nl; Two Cantrips. You learn two cantrips of your choice from the Cleric, Druid, or Wizard spell list. Intelligence, Wisdom or Charisma is your spellcasting ability for th is feat's spells (choose when you select this feat). &nl; Level 1 Spell. Choose a level 1 spell from the same list you selected for this feat's cantrips. You always have that spell prepared. You can cast it once without a spell slot, and you regain the ability to cast it in that way when you finish a Long Rest. You can also cast the spell using any spell slots you have. &nl; Spell Change. Whenever you gain a new level, you can replace one of the spells you chose for this feat with a different spell of the same level from the chosen spell list. &nl; Repeatable. You can take this feat more than once, but you must choose a different spell list each time.	STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NOCHOICE													BONUS:VAR|POOL_Magic_Initiate|1						SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Musician	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Origin	VISIBLE:YES																						DESC:You gain the following benefits. &nl; Instrument Training. You gain proficiency with three Musical Instruments of your choice. &nl; Encouraging Song. As you finish a Short or Long Rest, you can play a song on a Musical Instrument with which you have proficiency and give Heroic Inspiration to allies who hear the song. The number of allies you can affect in this way equals your Proficiency Bonus.																	BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Musical Instrument Proficiency|3			SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Savage Attacker	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Origin	VISIBLE:YES																						DESC:You've trained to deal particularly damaging strikes. Once per turn when you hit a target with a weapon, you can roll the weapon's damage dice twice and use either roll against the target.																				SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Skilled	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Origin	VISIBLE:YES																						DESC:You gain the following benefits. &nl; Skill Proficiency. You gain proficiency in three skills of your choice. &nl; Expertise. Choose one of the skills you gained proficiency with from this feat. Your proficiency bonus is doubled for any ability check you make that uses the chosen skill.	STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NOCHOICE													BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Skilled|3			SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Tavern Brawler	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Origin	VISIBLE:YES																						DESC:You gain the following benefits. &nl; Tavern Brawler. You are proficient with improvised weapons and unarmed strikes, which deal 1d4 damage. &nl; Grappler. You can use the Attack action to make a special melee attack to grapple a creature. If you’re able to make multiple attacks with the Attack action, this attack replaces one of them. &nl; Tavern Brawler’s Resilience. When you are hit by an attack or fail a saving throw and aren’t incapacitated, you can use your Reaction to roll a d12. Add your Constitution modifier to the number rolled, and reduce the damage by that total. You can use this feature only once per Long Rest.																				SOURCEPAGE:PHB	ASPECT:COMBAT|Unarmed Strike damage deal Bludgeoning damage equal to 1d4 plus your Strength modifier.
Tough	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Origin	VISIBLE:YES																						DESC:Your Hit Point maximum increases by an amount equal to twice your character level when you gain this feat. Whenever you gain a character level thereafter, your Hit Point maximum increases by an additional 2 Hit Points.											BONUS:HP|CURRENTMAX|2*HD									SOURCEPAGE:PHB

###Block: General Feats
# Feat Name	CATEGORY:	TYPE:	visible	key	Req. Att.	Required Class	Required Feat				Req. nb of Hand	Required Lvl	Required Skill	Req. Spellbook		Required Stat						Var. Min. Value	Special Ability	Define	DESC:	Stackable?	Multiple?	Choose	Automaticaly Gained Armor Prof.	Automaticaly Gained Shield Prof.	Automaticaly Gained Weapon Prof.	Add Spell Lvl	Save checks bonus	Combat bonus	BONUS:DC	Bonus to HP	% bonus to range	Bonus to skill	Modify VAR	Weapon prop. bonus	Weapon prof. bonus	Source Page					
Ability Score Improvement	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Origin	VISIBLE:YES																						DESC:Your ability scores each increase by 2, or you can increase one ability score by 4. You can't increase an ability score above 20 using this feat.	STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NOCHOICE													BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Ability Score Increase +1|2								SOURCEPAGE:PHB	
Actor	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES		PRECLASS:1,TYPE.Base=4	PRESTAT:1,CHA=13																			DESC:You gain the following benefits. &nl; Ability Score Increase. Increase your Charisma score by 1, to a maximum of 20. &nl; Impersonation. While you're disguised as a real or fictional person, you have Advantage on Charisma (Deception or Performance) checks to convince others that you are that person. &nl; Mimicry. You can mimic the sounds of other creatures, including speech. A creature that hears the mimicry must succeed on a Wisdom (Insight) check to determine the effect is faked (DC 8 plus your Charisma modifier and Proficiency Bonus).	DEFINE:MimicryDC|0																BONUS:STAT|CHA|1	BONUS:VAR|MimicryDC|8+CHA+ProficiencyBonus		SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Athlete	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES		PRECLASS:1,TYPE.Base=4	PRESTAT:1,STR=13,DEX=13																			DESC:You gain the following benefits. &nl; Ability Score Increase. Increase your Strength or Dexterity score by 1, to a maximum of 20. &nl; Climb Speed. You gain a Climb Speed equal to your Speed. &nl; Hop Up. When you have the Prone condition, you can right yourself with only 5 feet of movement. &nl; Jumping. You can make a running Long or High Jump after moving only 5 feet.					BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Athlete Stats|1	MOVECLONE:Walk,Climb,*1														SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Charger	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES		PRECLASS:1,TYPE.Base=4	PRESTAT:1,STR=13,DEX=13																			DESC:You gain the following benefits. &nl; Ability Score Increase. Increase your Strength or Dexterity score by 1, to a maximum of 20. &nl; Improved Dash. When you take the Dash action, your Speed increases by 10 feet for that action. &nl; Charge Attack. If you move at least 10 feet in a straight line toward a target immediately before hitting it with a melee attack roll as part of the Attack action, choose one of the following effects: gain a 1d8 bonus to the attack's damage roll, or push the target up to 10 feet away if it is no more than one size larger than you. You can use this benefit only once on each of your turns.					BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Charger Stats|1	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Chef	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES		PRECLASS:1,TYPE.Base=4																				DESC:You gain the following benefits. Ability Score Increase. Increase your Constitution or Wisdom score by 1, to a maximum of 20. &nl; Cook's Utensils. You gain proficiency with Cook's Utensils if you don't already have it. &nl; Replenishing Meal. As par t of a Short Rest, you can cook special food if you have ingredients and Cook's Utensils on hand. You can prepare enough of this food for a number of creatures equal to 4 plus your Proficiency Bonus. At the end of the Short Rest, any creature who eats the fo od and spends one or more Hit Dice to regain Hit Points regains an extra 1d8 Hit Points. &nl; Bolstering Treats. With 1 hou r of work or when you finish a Long Rest, you ca n cook a number of treats equal to your Proficiency Bon us if you have ingredients and Cook's Utensils on hand. These special treats last 8 hours after being made. A creature can use a Bonus Action to eat one of those t reats to gain a number of Temporary Hit Points equal to your Proficiency Bonus.					BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Cook Stats|1	SOURCEPAGE:PHB	ABILITY:Internal|AUTOMATIC|Tool Proficiency ~ Cook's Utensils
Crossbow Expert	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES		PRECLASS:1,TYPE.Base=4	PRESTAT:1,DEX=13																			DESC:You gain the following benefits. &nl;Ability Score Increase. Increase your Dexterity score by 1, to a maximum of 20. &nl; Ignore Loading. You ignore the Loading property of the Hand Crossbow, Heavy Crossbow, and Light Crossbow (a ll called crossbows elsewhere in this feat). If you're holding one of them, you can load a piece of ammunition into it even if you lack a free hand. &nl; Firing in Melee. Being within 5 feet of an enemy doesn't impose Disadvantage on your attack rolls with crossbows. &nl; Dual Wielding. When you make the extra attack of the Light property, you can add your ability modifier to the damage of the extra attack if that at- tack is with a crossbow that has the Light property and you aren't already adding that modifier to the damage.					BONUS:STAT|DEX|1	BONUS:COMBAT|SECONDARYDAMAGE|DEX| PREEQUIPSECONDARY:1,TYPE=Crossbow.Light	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Crusher	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES		PRECLASS:1,TYPE.Base=4	PRESTAT:1,STR=13																			DESC:You gain the following benefits. &nl; Ability Score Increase. Increase your Strength or Constitution score by 1, to a maximum of 20. &nl; Push. Once per turn, when you hit a creature with an attack that deals Bludgeoning damage, you can move it 5 feet to an unoccupied space if the target is no more than one size larger than you. &nl; Enhanced Critical. When you score a Critical Hit that deals Bludgeoning damage to a creature, attack rolls against that creature have Advantage until the start of your next turn.				BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Crusher Stats|1	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Defensive Duelist	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES		PRECLASS:1,TYPE.Base=4	PRESTAT:1,DEX=13																			DESC:You gain the following benefits. &nl; Ability Score Increase. Increase your Dexterity score by 1, to a maximum of 20. &nl; Parry. If you're holding a Finesse weapon and another creature hits you with a melee attack, you can take a Reaction to add your Proficiency Bonus to your Armor Class, potentially causing the attack to miss you. You gain this bonus to your AC against me lee attacks until the start of your next turn.					BONUS:STAT|DEX|1	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Dual Wielder	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES		PRECLASS:1,TYPE.Base=4	PRESTAT:1,STR=13,DEX=13																			DESC:You gain the following benefits. &nl; Ability Score Increase. Increase your Strength or Dexterity score by 1, to a maximum of 20. &nl; Enhanced Dual Wielding. When you take the Attack action on your turn and attack with a weapon that has the Light property, you can make one extra attack as a Bonus Action later on the same turn with a different weapon, which must be a Melee weapon that lacks the Two-Handed property. You don't add your ability modifier to the extra attack's damage unless that modifier is negative. &nl; Quick Draw. You can draw or stow two weapons that lack the Two-Handed property when you would normally be able to draw or stow only one.					BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Dual Wielder Stats|1		SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Durable	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES		PRECLASS:1,TYPE.Base=4																				DESC:You gain the following benefits. &nl; Ability Score Increase. Increase your Constitution score by 1, to a maximum of 20. &nl; Defy Death. You have Advantage on Death Saving Throws. &nl; Speedy Recovery. As a Bonus Action, you can expend one of your Hit Point Dice, roll the die, and regain a number of Hit Points equal to the roll.					BONUS:STAT|CON|1	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Elemental Adept	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES		PRECLASS:1,TYPE.Base=4	PREMULT:1,[PRECLASS:1,SPELLCASTER=1],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Warlock ~ Pact Magic]																			DESC:ou gain the following benefits. &nl; Ability Score Increase. Increase your Intelligence, Wisdom, or Charisma score by 1. to a maximum of 20. &nl; Energy Mastery. Choose one of the following damage types: Acid, Cold, Fire, Lightning, or Thunder. Spells you cast ignore Resistance to damage of the chosen type. In addition, when you roll damage for a spell you cast that deals damage of that type, you can treat any 1 on a damage die as a 2. &nl; Repeatable. You can take this feat more than once, but you must choose a different damage type each time for Energy Mastery.	STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NOCHOICE	BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Elemental Adept Stats|1	BONUS:VAR|POOL_Elemental_Adept|1	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Fey-Touched	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES		PRECLASS:1,TYPE.Base=4																				DESC:Your exposure to the Feywild's magic grants you the following benefits. &nl;Ability Score Increase. Increase your Intelligence, Wisdom, or Charisma score by 1, to a maximum of 20. &nl; Fey Magic. Choose one level 1 spell from the Divination or Enchantment school of magic. You always have that spell and the Misty Step spell prepared. You can cast each of these spells without expending a spell slot. Once you cast either spell in this way, you can't cast that spell in this way again until you finish a Long Rest. You can also cast these spells using spell slots you have of the appropriate level. The spells' spelkasting ability is the ability increased by this feat.			CHOOSE:NOCHOICE	BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Fey Touched Stats|1	BONUS:VAR|POOL_Fey_Touched_Spell|1					SOURCEPAGE:PHB	SPELLS:Fey Touched|TIMES=1|CASTERLEVEL=1|Misty Step
Grappler	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES		PRECLASS:1,TYPE.Base=4	PRESTAT:1,STR=13,DEX=13																			DESC:You gain the following benefits. &nl; Ability Score Increase. Increase your Strength or Dexterity score by 1, to a maximum of 20. &nl; Punch and Grab. When you hit a creature with an Unarmed Strike as part of the Attack action on your turn, you can use both the Damage and the Grapple option. You can use this benefit only once per turn. &nl; Attack Advantage. You have Advantage on attack rolls against a creature Grappled by you. &nl; Fast Wrestler. Your Speed isn't halved when you move a creature Grappled by you if the creature is your size or smaller.					BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Grappler Stats|1	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Great Weapon Master	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES		PRECLASS:1,TYPE.Base=4	PRESTAT:1,STR=13																			DESC:You gain the following benefits. &nl; Ability Score Increase. Increase your Strength score by 1, to a maximum of 20. &nl; Heavy Weapon Mastery. When you hit a creature with a weapon that has the Heavy property as part of the Attack action on your turn, you can cause the weapon to deal extra damage to the target. The extra damage equals your Proficiency Bonus. &nl; Hew. Immediately after you score a Critical Hit with a Melee weapon or reduce a creature to O Hit Points with one, you can make one attack with the same weapon as a Bonus Action.				BONUS:STAT|STR|1	 	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Heavily Armored	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES		PRECLASS:1,TYPE.Base=4	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,TYPE.ArmorProfMedium																				DESC:You gain the following benefits. &nl; Ability Score Increase. Increase your Constitution or Strength score by 1, to a maximum of 20. &nl; Armor Training. You gain training with Heavy armor.					BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Heavily Armored Stats|1	ABILITY:Internal|AUTOMATIC|TYPE.ArmorProfHeavy		SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Heavy Armor Master	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES		PRECLASS:1,TYPE.Base=4	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Internal,TYPE.ArmorProfHeavy																				DESC:You gain the following benefits. &nl; Ability Score Increase. Increase your Constitution or Strength score by 1, to a maximum of 20. &nl; Damage Reduction. When you're hit by an attack while you're wearing Heavy armor, any Bludgeoning, Piercing, and Slashing damage dealt to you by that attack is reduced by an amount equal to your Proficiency Bonus.					BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Heavy Armor Master Stats|1	DR:0/-	BONUS:DR|-|ProficiencyBonus|PREEQUIP:1,TYPE=Armor.Heavy		SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Inspiring Leader	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES		PRECLASS:1,TYPE.Base=4	PRESTAT:1,WIS=13,CHA=13																			DESC:You gain the following benefits. &nl; Ability Score Increase. Increase your Wisdom or Charisma score by 1, to a maximu m of 20. &nl; Bolstering Performance. When you finish a Short or Long Rest, you can give an inspiring performance: a speech, song, or dance. When you do so, choose up to six allies (which can include yourself) within 30 feet of yourself who witness t he performance. The chosen creat ures each gain Temporary Hit Points equal to your ch aracter level plus the modifier of the ability you increased with this feat.					BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Inspiring Leader|1	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Keen Mind	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES		PRECLASS:1,TYPE.Base=4	PRESTAT:1,INT=13																			DESC:You gain t he foll owing benefits. &nl; Ability Score Increase. Increase your Intelligence score by 1, to a maximum of 20. &nl; Lore Knowledge. Choose one of the following skills: Arcana , History, Investigation, Nature, or Religion. If you lack proficiency in the chosen skill, you gain proficiency in it, and if you already have proficiency in it, you gain Expertise in it. &nl; Quick Study. You can take the Study action as a Bonus Action.					BONUS:STAT|INT|1	BONUS:VAR|POOL_Keen_Mind_Skills|1	SOURCEPAGE:PHB	
Lightly Armored	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES		PRECLASS:1,TYPE.Base=4																					DESC:You gain the following benefits. &nl; Ability Score Increase. Increase your Strength or Dexterity score by 1, to a maximum of 20. &nl; Armor Training. You gain training with Light armor and Shields.					BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Lightly Armored Stats|1	ABILITY:Internal|AUTOMATIC|TYPE.ArmorProfLight|TYPE.ShieldProf		SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Mage Slayer	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES		PRECLASS:1,TYPE.Base=4																				DESC:You gain the following benefits. &nl; Ability Score Increase. Increase your Strength or Dexterity score by 1, to a maximum of 20. &nl; Concentration Breaker. When you damage a creature that is concentrating, it has Disadvantage on the saving throw it makes to maintain Concentration. &nl; Guarded Mind. If you fail an Intelligence, a Wisdom , or a Charisma saving throw, you can cause yourself to succeed instead. Once you use this benefit, you can't use it again until you finish a Short or Long Rest.					BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Mage Slayer Stats|1	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Martial Weapon Training	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES		PRECLASS:1,TYPE.Base=4																					DESC:You gain t he follow ing benefits. &nl; Ability Score Increase. Increase your Strength or Dexterity score by 1, to a maximum of 20. &nl; Weapon Proficiency. You gain proficiency with Martial weapons.					BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Martial Weapon Training Stats|1	ABILITY:Internal|AUTOMATIC|TYPE.WeaponProfMartial		SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Medium Armor Master	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES		PRECLASS:1,TYPE.Base=4	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Internal,TYPE.ArmorProfMedium																				DESC:You gain the followi ng benefits. &nl; Ability Score In crease. Increase your Strength or Dexterity score by 1, to a maximum of 20. &nl; Dexterous Wearer. While you're wearing Medium armor, you can add 3, rather than 2, to your AC if you have a Dexterity score of 16 or higher.					BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Medium Armor Master Stats|1	BONUS:COMBAT|AC|1|PRESTAT:1,DEX=16			SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Moderately Armored	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES		PRECLASS:1,TYPE.Base=4	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Internal,TYPE.ArmorProfLight																				DESC:You gain the following benefits. &nl; Ability Score Increase. Increase your Strength or Dexterity score by 1, to a maximum of 20. &nl; Armor Training. You gain training with Medium armor.					BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Moderately Armored Stats|1	ABILITY:Internal|AUTOMATIC|TYPE.ArmorProfMedium		SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Mounted Combatant	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES		PRECLASS:1,TYPE.Base=4																				DESC:You gain the following benefits. &nl; Ability Score Increase. Increase your Strength, Dexterity, or Wisdom score by 1, to a maximum of 20. &nl; Mounted Strike. While mounted, you have Advantage on attack rolls against any unmounted creature within 5 feet of your mount that is at least one size smaller than the mount. &nl; Leap Aside. If your mount is subjected to an effect that allows it to make a Dexterity saving throw to take only half damage, it instead takes no damage if it succeeds on the saving throw and only half damage if it fails. For your mount to gain this benefit, you must be riding it, and neither of you can have the Incapacitated condition. &nl; Veer. While mounted, you can force an attack that hits your mount to hit you instead if you don't have the Incapacitated condition.					BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Mounted Combatant Stats|1	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Observant	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES		PRECLASS:1,TYPE.Base=4	PRESTAT:1,INT=13,WIS=13																			DESC:You gain the following benefits. &nl; Ability Score Increase. Increase your Intelligence or Wisdom score by 1, to a maximum of 20. &nl; Keen Observer. Choose one of the following skills: Insight, Investigation, or Perception. If you lack proficiency with the chosen skill, you gain proficiency in it, and if you already have proficiency in it, you gain Expertise in it. &nl; Quick Search. You can take the Search action as a Bonus Action.	DEFINE:ObservantDC|0																BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Observant Stats|1	BONUS:VAR|POOL_Observant_Skills|1			SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Piercer	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES		PRECLASS:1,TYPE.Base=4																				DESC:You gain the following benefits. &nl; Ability Score Increase. Increase your Strength or Dexterity by 1, to a maximum of 20. &nl; Puncture. Once per turn, when you hit a creature with an attack that deals Piercing damage, you can reroll one of the attack's damage dice, and you must use the new roll. &nl; Enhanced Critical. When you score a Critical Hit that deals Piercing damage to a creature, you can roll one additional damage die when determining the extra Piercing damage the target takes.				BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Piercer Stats|1	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Poisoner	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES		PRECLASS:1,TYPE.Base=4																				DESC:You gain the following benefits. &nl; Ability Score Increase. Increase your Dexterity or Intelligence score by 1, to a maximum of 20. &nl; Potent Poison. When you make a damage roll that deals Poison damage, it ignores Resistance to Poison damage. &nl; Brew Poison. You gain proficiency with the Poisoner's Kit. With 1 hour of work using such a kit and expending 50 GP worth of materials, you can create a number of poison doses equal to your Proficiency Bonus. As a Bonus Action, you can apply a poison dose to a weapon or piece of ammunition. Once applied, the poison retains its potency for 1 minute or until you hit with the poisoned item, whichever is shorter. When a creature takes damage from the poisoned item, that creature must succeed on a Constitution saving throw (DC 8 plus the modifier of the ability increased by this feat and your Proficiency Bonus) or take 2d8 Poison damage and have the Poisoned condition until the end of your next turn.	DEFINE:PoisonDC|0			BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Poisoner Stats|1	ABILITY:Internal|AUTOMATIC|Tool Proficiency ~ Poisoner's Kit		SOURCEPAGE:PHB	BONUS:VAR|PoisonDC|SpellDC_Dex|PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Internal,Poisoner ~ Dexterity	BONUS:VAR|PoisonDC|SpellDC_Int|PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Internal,Poisoner ~ Intelligence
Polearm Master	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES		PRECLASS:1,TYPE.Base=4	PRESTAT:1,STR=13,DEX=13																			DESC:You gain the following benefits . &nl; Ability Score Increase. Increase you r Dexterity or Strength score by 1, to a maximum of 20. &nl; Pole Strike. Immediately after you take the Attack action and attack with a Quarterstaff, a Spear, or a weapon that has the Heavy and Reach properties, you can use a Bonus Action to make a melee attack with the opposite end of the weapon. The weapon deals Bludgeoning damage, and the weapon's damage die for this attack is a d4. &nl; Reactive Strike. While you're holding a Quarterstaff, a Spear, or a weapon that has the Heavy and Reach properties, you can take a Reaction to make one melee attack against a creature that enters the reach you have with that weapon.					BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Polearm Master Stats|1	 	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Resilient	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES		PRECLASS:1,TYPE.Base=4																				DESC:You gain the following benefits. &nl; Ability Score Increase. Choose one ability in which you lack saving throw proficiency. Increase the chosen ability score by 1, to a maximum of 20. &nl; Saving Throw Proficiency. You gain saving throw proficiency with the chosen ability.					BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Resilient Stats|1			SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Ritual Caster	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES		PRECLASS:1,TYPE.Base=4	PRESTAT:1,INT=13,WIS=13,CHA=13																			DESC:You gain the following benefits. Ability Score Increase. Increase your Intelligence, Wisdom, or Charisma score by 1, to a maximum of 20. &nl; Ritual Spells. Choose a number of level 1 spells equal to your Proficiency Bonus that have the Ritual tag. You always have those spells prepared, and you can cast them with any spell slots you have. The spells' spellcasting ability is the ability increased by this feat . Whenever your Proficiency Bonus increases thereafter, you can add an additional level 1 spell with the Ritual tag to the spells always prepared with this feature. &nl; Quick Ritual. With this benefit, you can cast a Ritual spell that you have prepared using its regular casting time rather than the extended time for a Ritual. Doing so doesn't requ ire a spell slot. Once you cast the spell in th is way, you can't use th is benefit again until you fini sh a Long Rest.					BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Ritual Caster Stats|1	BONUS:VAR|POOL_Ritual_Caster_Spells|ProficiencyBonus			SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Sentinel	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES		PRECLASS:1,TYPE.Base=4	PRESTAT:1,TYPE.Strength=13,DEX=13																			DESC:You gain the following benefits. &nl; Ability Score Increase. Increase your Strength or Dexterity score by 1, to a maximum of 20. &nl; Guardian. Immediately after a creature within 5 feet of you takes the Disengage action or hits a target other than you with an attack, you can make an Opportunity Attack against that creature. &nl; Halt. When you hit a creature with an Opportunity Attack, the creature's Speed becomes O for the rest of the current turn.					BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Sentinel Stats|1	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Shadow-Touched	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES		PRECLASS:1,TYPE.Base=4																				DESC:Your exposure to the Shadowfell's magic grants you the following benefits. &nl; Ability Score Increase. Increase your Intelligence, Wisdom, or Charisma score by 1, to a maximum of 20. &nl; Shadow Magic. Choose one level 1 spell from the Illusion or Necromancy school of magic. You always have that spell and the Invisibility spell prepared. You can cast each of these spells without expending a spell slot. Once you cast either spell in this way, you can't cast that spell in this way again until you finish a Long Rest. You can also cast these spells using spell slots you have of the appropriate level. The spells' spellcasting ability is the ability increased by this feat.		BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Shadow-Touched Stats|1	BONUS:VAR|POOL_Shadow_Touched_Spell|1					SOURCEPAGE:PHB	SPELLS:Shadow-Touched|TIMES=1|CASTERLEVEL=1|Invisibility
Sharpshooter	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES	PRECLASS:1,TYPE.Base=4	PRESTAT:1,DEX=13																			DESC:You gain the following benefits. &nl; Ability Score Increase. Increase your Dexterity score by 1, to a maximum of 20. &nl; By pass Cover. Your ranged attacks with weapons ignore Half Cover and Three-Quarters Cover. &nl; Firing in Melee. Being within 5 feet of an enemy doesn't impose Disadvantage on your attack rolls with Ranged weapons . &nl; Long Shots. Attacking at long range doesn't impose Disadvantage on your attack rolls with Ranged weapons.	BONUS:STAT|DEX|1					SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Shield Master	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES	PRECLASS:1,TYPE.Base=4	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Internal,TYPE.ShieldProf																			DESC:You gain the following benefits. &nl; Ability Score Increase. Increase your Strength score by 1, to a maximum of 20. &nl; Shield Bash. If you attack a creature within 5 feet of you as part of the Attack action and hit with a Melee weapon, you can immediately bash the target with your Shield if it's equipped, forcing the target to make a Strength saving throw (DC 8 plus your Strength modifier and Proficiency Bonus). On a failed save , you either push the target 5 feet from you or cause it to have the Prone condition {your choice). You can use this benefit only once on each of your turns. &nl; Interpose Shield. If you're subjected to an effect that allows you to make a Dexterity saving throw to take only half damage, you can take a Reaction to take no damage if you succeed on the saving throw and are holding a Shield.	DEFINE:ShieldBashDC|0	BONUS:STAT|STR|1	BONUS:VAR|ShieldBashDC|SpellDC_Str			SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Skill Expert	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES	PRECLASS:1,TYPE.Base=4																				DESC:You gain the following benefits. &nl; Ability Score Increase. Increase one ability score of your choice by 1, to a max imum of 20. &nl; Skill Proficiency. You gain proficiency in one skill of your choice. &nl; Expertise. Choose one skill in w hich you have proficiency but lack Expertise. You gain Expertise with that skill.		BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Skill Expert Stats|1	BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Skill Proficiency|1	BONUS:VAR|POOL_Expertise|1		SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Skulker	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES	PRECLASS:1,TYPE.Base=4	PRESTAT:1,DEX=13																			DESC:You gain the following benefits. Ability Score Increase. Increase your Dexterity score by 1, to a maximum of 20. Blindsight. You have Blindsight with a range of 10 feet. &nl; Fog of War. You exploit the distractions of battle, gaining Advantage on any Dexterity (Stealth) check you make as part of the Hide action during combat. &nl; Sniper. If you make an attack roll while hidden and the roll misses, making the attack roll doesn't reveal your location.		BONUS:STAT|DEX|1	BONUS:VAR|BlindsightRange|10			SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Slasher	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES	PRECLASS:1,TYPE.Base=4																					DESC:You gain the following benefits. Ability Score Increase. Increase your Strength or Dexterity score by 1, to a maximum of 20. &nl; Hamstring. Once per turn when you hit a creature with an attack that deals Slashing damage, you can reduce the Speed of that creature by 10 feet until the start of your next turn. &nl; Enhanced Critical. When you score a Critical Hit that deals Slashing damage to a creature, it has Disadvantage on attack rolls until the start of your next turn.		BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Slasher Stats|1					SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Speedy	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES	PRECLASS:1,TYPE.Base=4	PRESTAT:1,DEX=13,CON=13																		DESC:You gain the following benefits. Ability Score Increase. Increase your Dexterity or Constitution score by 1, to a maximum of 20. &nl; Speed Increase. Your Speed increases by 10 feet. &nl; Dash over Difficult Terrain. When you take the Dash action on your turn, Difficult Terrain doesn't cost you extra movement for the rest of that turn. &nl; Agile Movement. Oppor tunit y Attacks have Disadvantage against you.		BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Speedy Stats|1	BONUS:MOVEADD|TYPE.Walk|10	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Spell Sniper	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES		PRECLASS:1,TYPE.Base=4	PREMULT:1,[PRECLASS:1,SPELLCASTER=1],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Warlock ~ Pact Magic]																			DESC:You gain the following benefits. Ability Score Increase. Increase your Intelligence, Wisdom, or Charisma score by 1, to a max imum of 20. &nl; Bypass Cover. Your attack rolls for spells ignore Half Cover and Three-Quarters Cover. &nl; Casting in Melee. Being within 5 feet of an enemy doesn't impose Disadvantage on your attack rolls with spells. &nl; Increased Range. When you cast a spell that has a range of at least 10 feet and requires you to make an attack roll, you can increase the spell's range by 60 feet.	BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Spell Sniper Stats|1				SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Telekinetic	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES		PRECLASS:1,TYPE.Base=4																				DESC:You gain the following benefits. &nl; Ability Score Increase. Increase your Intelligence, Wisdom, or Charisma score by 1, to a maximum of 20. &nl; Minor Telekinesis. You learn the Mage Hand spell. You can cast it without Verbal or Somatic components, you can make the spectral hand Invisible, and its range increases by 30 feet when you cast it. The spell's spelkasting ability is the ability increased by this feat. &nl; Telekinetic Shove. As a Bonus Action, you can telekinetically shove one creature you can see within 30 fee t of yourself. When you do so, the target must succeed on a Strength saving throw (DC 8 plus the ability modifier of the score increased by this feat and your Proficiency Bonus) or be moved 5 feet toward or away from you.	DEFINE:TelekineticDC|0	BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Telekinetic Stats|1	SOURCEPAGE:PHB	BONUS:VAR|TelekineticDC|SpellDC_Int|PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Internal,Telekinesis ~ Intelligence	BONUS:VAR|TelekineticDC|SpellDC_Wis|PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Internal,Telekinesis ~ Wisdom	BONUS:VAR|TelekineticDC|SpellDC_Cha|PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Internal,Telekinesis ~ Charisma	SPELLS:Telekinetic|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Mage Hand,TelekineticDC
Telepathic	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES		PRECLASS:1,TYPE.Base=4																				DESC:You gain the follow ing benefits. &nl; Ability Score Increase. Increase your Intelligence, Wisdom , or Charisma score by 1, to a maximum of 20. &nl; Telepathic Utterance. You can speak telepathically to any creat ure you can see w ith in 6 0 feet of yourself. Your telepathic utterances are in a la nguage you know, and the creature understa nds you only if it knows that language. Your communication doesn't give the creature the ability lo respond to you telepathically. &nl; Detect Th oughts. You always have the Detect Tlioughts spell prepared. You can cast it without a spell slot or spell components, and you must finish a Long Rest before you can cast it in this way again. You can also cast it using spell slots you have of the appropriate level. Your spellcasting ability for the spell is the ability increased by this feat.	DEFINE:TelepathicDC|0	BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Telepathic Stats|1	BONUS:VAR|TelepathyRange|60	SOURCEPAGE:PHB	BONUS:VAR|TelepathicDC|SpellDC_Int|PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Internal,Telepathic ~ Intelligence	BONUS:VAR|TelepathicDC|SpellDC_Wis|PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Internal,Telepathic ~ Wisdom	BONUS:VAR|TelepathicDC|SpellDC_Cha|PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Internal,Telepathic ~ Charisma	SPELLS:Telepathic|TIMES=1|CASTERLEVEL=1|Detect Thought,TelepathicDC
War Caster	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES		PRECLASS:1,TYPE.Base=4	PREMULT:1,[PRECLASS:1,SPELLCASTER=1],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Warlock ~ Pact Magic]																				DESC:You gain the following benefits. &nl; Ability Score Increase. Increase your Intelligence, Wisdom, or Charisma score by 1, to a maximum of 20. &nl; Concentration. You have Advantage on Constitution saving throws that you make to maintain Concentration. &nl; Reactive Spell. When a creature provokes an Opportunity Attack from you by leaving your reach, you can take a Reaction to cast a spell at the creature rather than making an Opportunity Attack. The spell must have a casting time of one action and must target only that creature. &nl; Somatic Components. You can perform the Somatic components of spells even when you have weapons or a Shield in one or both hands.					BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|War Caster Stats|1			SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Weapon Master	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES		PRECLASS:1,TYPE.Base=4																				DESC:You gain the following benefits. &nl; Ability Score Increase. Increase your Strength or Dexterity score by 1, to a maximum of 20. &nl; Mastery Property. Your training with weapons allows you to use the mastery property of one kind of Simple or Martial weapon of your choice, provided you have proficiency with it. Whenever you finish a Long Rest, you can change the kind of weapon to another eligible kind.					BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Weapon Master Stats|1	BONUS:VAR|POOL_Weapon_Mastery|1		SOURCEPAGE:PHB

